The ending is indeed bittersweet. But according to pg 33, my headcanon is that Kokomi end up ran away with the MC, being his GF so he don't need to "pay" for her service anymore and use those for her well-being and send it to her family from time to time instead. The rest is a typical story about working-class young couple in a rural area, you know, got pregnant around 18, got married, she took care of the child, he got full-time job, etc. It's... very realistic to me if not by those messed-up child prostitute part, same as the author's other work "1989". I'd say they have such great ability telling us a slice of life story with very weird fantasy coated on top. One of my most favorite so far.

I think this doujin is emblematic of what I would like to call "Sugar Life", or "Sugar Life Effect".
Named after "Happy Sugar Life", it refers to when you have a story with a fucked up premise, but there's that tinge of wholesomeness, and by the end you are either touched by the wholesomeness ramping up, or left with a really bittersweet feeling. 

Btw, I recommend watching Happy Sugar Life. I feel it's well made and delivers an interesting and compelling story.
